Dia. 03 Wrong Vital Point
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red255\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White 1 in this diagram has the same meaning as White 1 has in Dia. 01. Both moves expand the living space. Usually these moves are powerful, but this time they are \cf1\b wrong\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par Black's throw-in at 2 is sharp. White can't live after this move.
\par If White plays at A, Black's placement at B is the deciding move.
\par
\par }
